Most properties will only change when the vehicle is bought, serviced (enters a depot), visits a station or on loading of a saved game. Other ones such as TE are called every time a TE calculation is run.

If the callback fails, the corresponding value from the action 0 property will be used. The callback is always used when defined, no bit in the action 0 property needs to be set to activate it.

Before r1758 (both 2.5 and TTDPatch 2.6), [[en/Callbacks#change-vehicle-properties-36 |callback 36]] was sometimes called with the 40+x and 80+x variables unavailable when they should have been available, or with not all 80+x variables properly initialized, causing some 40+x variables to be unsafe.

Informacje o właściwościach pojemności można również znaleźć na stronie podsumowania [[pl/Development/NewGRF/NFO Specs/VehicleRefitting|vehicle refitting]].
